.TH "CUSTOMELEMENTREGISTRY.INITIALIZE" "3JS" "February 23, 2026" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
CustomElementRegistry.initialize \- CustomElementRegistry: initialize()
method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]initialize()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]CustomElementRegistry\f[R] interface associates this registry with
a DOM subtree, setting the \f[CR]customElementRegistry\f[R] of each
inclusive descendant that doesn\(cqt already have one, and attempting to
upgrade any custom elements found.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
initialize(root)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]root\f[R]
A \f[CR]Node\f[R] object (typically a \f[CR]Document\f[R],
\f[CR]ShadowRoot\f[R], or \f[CR]Element\f[R]) whose inclusive
descendants will be associated with this registry.
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]NotSupportedError\f[R] \f[B]DOMException\f[R]
Thrown if this \f[CR]CustomElementRegistry\f[R] is not scoped (i.e., not
created with \f[CR]new CustomElementRegistry()\f[R]) and either
\f[CR]root\f[R] is a \f[CR]Document\f[R] node or \f[CR]root\f[R]\(cqs
node document\(cqs \f[CR]customElementRegistry\f[R] is not this
\f[CR]CustomElementRegistry\f[R].
.SH DESCRIPTION
When \f[CR]initialize()\f[R] is called, it walks through the inclusive
descendants of \f[CR]root\f[R] in tree order.
For each element (or \f[CR]Document\f[R]/\f[CR]ShadowRoot\f[R] at the
root) that has a \f[CR]null\f[R] \f[CR]customElementRegistry\f[R], it
sets that registry to this \f[CR]CustomElementRegistry\f[R].
It then attempts to upgrade each element whose
\f[CR]customElementRegistry\f[R] matches this registry.
.PP
Once a node\(cqs \f[CR]customElementRegistry\f[R] is set to a
\f[CR]CustomElementRegistry\f[R] object, it cannot be changed.
This means \f[CR]initialize()\f[R] can only set the registry on nodes
where it is still \f[CR]null\f[R].
However, it will still attempt to upgrade any element whose
\f[CR]customElementRegistry\f[R] already matches this registry, not just
elements that were freshly assigned.
.PP
Nodes have a \f[CR]null\f[R] custom element registry in several
situations, including:
.IP \(bu 2
Documents created by \f[CR]DOMImplementation.createHTMLDocument()\f[R],
whose custom element registry is \f[CR]null\f[R] by default.
Elements created within such documents also have \f[CR]null\f[R]
registries.
.IP \(bu 2
Shadow roots created with \f[CR]customElementRegistry\f[R] set to
\f[CR]null\f[R] via \f[CR]Element.attachShadow()\f[R].
.IP \(bu 2
Declarative shadow roots created from a \f[CR]<template>\f[R] element
with the \f[CR]shadowrootcustomelementregistry\f[R] attribute, which
instructs the HTML parser to leave the shadow root\(cqs custom element
registry as \f[CR]null\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Initializing a shadow root with a scoped registry
This example creates a shadow root without a custom element registry,
adds HTML containing a custom element, and then calls
\f[CR]initialize()\f[R] to associate a scoped registry.
The \f[CR]<my\-element>\f[R] element is upgraded when
\f[CR]initialize()\f[R] sets the registry on the shadow root and its
descendants.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] myRegistry = \f[B]new\f[R] CustomElementRegistry();
myRegistry.define(
  \(dqmy\-element\(dq,
  \f[B]class\f[R] \f[B]extends\f[R] HTMLElement {
    connectedCallback() {
      \f[B]this\f[R].textContent = \(dqHello from scoped registry!\(dq;
    }
  },
);

\f[B]const\f[R] host = document.createElement(\(dqdiv\(dq);
document.body.appendChild(host);

\f[I]// Create the shadow DOM structure without a registry\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] shadow = host.attachShadow({
  mode: \(dqopen\(dq,
  customElementRegistry: \f[B]null\f[R],
});
shadow.innerHTML = \(dq<my\-element></my\-element>\(dq;

\f[I]// Later, associate the scoped registry and upgrade custom elements\f[R]
myRegistry.initialize(shadow);

console.log(shadow.querySelector(\(dqmy\-element\(dq).textContent);
\f[I]// \(dqHello from scoped registry!\(dq\f[R]
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
Using custom elements
.IP \(bu 2
